---
import BaseLayout from '@layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="China Sourcing Guide"
  description="A practical China sourcing hub for small business importers covering product specs, supplier comparison, samples, payment terms, QC, and shipment preparation."
  canonical="/china-sourcing/"
>
  <section class="content-page">
    <div class="hub-hero">
      <div class="page-header">
        <span class="eyebrow">China sourcing</span>
        <h1>Find better suppliers and avoid beginner sourcing mistakes.</h1>
        <p>
          Sourcing goes better when you define the product clearly, compare suppliers on the same terms, test samples,
          and plan quality checks before shipment.
        </p>
        <div class="inline-actions">
          <a class="button" href="/tools/supplier-comparison-sheet/">Open comparison sheet</a>
          <a class="button secondary" href="/blog/china-sourcing-checklist-small-business/">Read sourcing checklist</a>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="hub-visual" aria-label="China sourcing preparation summary">
        <div class="hub-stat"><span class="icon-badge">S</span><div><strong>Spec</strong><p>Write product details before asking for quotes.</p></div></div>
        <div class="hub-stat"><span class="icon-badge">3</span><div><strong>Compare</strong><p>Review multiple suppliers using the same fields.</p></div></div>
        <div class="hub-stat"><span class="icon-badge">QC</span><div><strong>Check</strong><p>Plan samples, inspection, and shipment details early.</p></div></div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="content-grid">
      <div class="prose">
        <h2>Who this guide is for</h2>
        <p>
          This guide is for small business importers, online sellers, wholesalers, and sourcing beginners who want to
          contact Chinese suppliers with clearer requirements and fewer expensive surprises.
        </p>

        <h2>Common problems sourcing beginners run into</h2>
        <ul class="checklist">
          <li>Asking for quotes before product specifications are clear</li>
          <li>Comparing suppliers without matching MOQ, trade terms, packaging, and lead time</li>
          <li>Skipping samples or approving samples without written notes</li>
          <li>Focusing only on unit price instead of total landed cost and risk</li>
          <li>Leaving quality control and shipment details until the last minute</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>What to prepare</h2>
        <ul class="checklist">
          <li>Product specifications with size, material, color, packaging, and target market</li>
          <li>A standard supplier comparison sheet</li>
          <li>Sample request notes and approval criteria</li>
          <li>Clear questions about MOQ, EXW, FOB, lead time, and payment terms</li>
          <li>A basic QC and shipment preparation checklist</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Helpful sourcing resources</h2>
        <div class="resource-grid">
          <a class="resource-card" href="/blog/china-sourcing-checklist-small-business/">
            <span class="card-kicker">Guide</span>
            <h3>Sourcing Checklist</h3>
            <p>Product specs, suppliers, samples, payment terms, QC, and shipment prep.</p>
            <strong>Read guide</strong>
          </a>
          <a class="resource-card" href="/tools/supplier-comparison-sheet/">
            <span class="card-kicker">Template</span>
            <h3>Supplier Sheet</h3>
            <p>Compare quotes and communication quality side by side.</p>
            <strong>Open template</strong>
          </a>
          <a class="resource-card" href="/tools/canton-fair-buyer-checklist/">
            <span class="card-kicker">Fair tool</span>
            <h3>Buyer Checklist</h3>
            <p>Useful if you are meeting suppliers at the Canton Fair.</p>
            <strong>Open checklist</strong>
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
      <aside class="sidebar">
        <div class="notice-box">
          <h2>Start with clear requirements</h2>
          <p>Start by clarifying whether your goal is travel planning, trade fair preparation, or supplier sourcing, then follow the guide that matches your trip.</p>
          <a class="button secondary" href="/blog/china-sourcing-checklist-small-business/">Read sourcing checklist</a>
        </div>
      </aside>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
